{
  "texts": [
    "To test whether caffeic acid and TcCSE were involved in defense response against P. palmivora, we performed a series of experiments.",
    "We first verified the function of TcCSE through heterologous overexpression in N. benthamiana, confirming the accumulation of caffeic acid both 48 and 96 h post transformation (Fig. 4B).",
    "Caffeic acid was inhibitory to P. palmivora mycelia (Fig. 4C).",
    "Despite these results, however, genotypes displaying upregulated TcCSE in our transcriptome experiment did not display increased caffeic acid accumulation in cacao leaves transiently expressing the gene (Fig. 4E).",
    "This result could be due to multiple factors."
  ]
}